skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "1827ab09-f5c3-4207-a327-92b8b65ac43b", "value": "A deposit that forms the ground surface (when the evidence is collected), particularly a hard surface such as a floor or road."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "78fc2770-e551-4df6-b304-7d73cfb4d465", "value": "EVIDENCE (EH)"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "ee69dfdd-aff3-44cd-b681-8950539ac46d", "value": "Terminology covering the existing physical remains of a monument, or the means by which a monument has been identified where no physical remains exist"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "78e19179-1e1e-492f-8465-9195899f0d3c", "value": "Monument visible as remains of former earthworks."}

{"id": "9807e3f7-742f-4754-bba9-65698480e81e", "value": "The deliberate deposit of a body in the ground, usually located in a special area set aside for the purpose of burial, such as a graveyard or cemetery."}

{"id": "3bc900d5-87cc-4fba-bd55-081e0c91fd71", "value": "A monument previously consisting of a built structure, but which has been demolished, such that only a ground plan and foundations or similar are thought to remain. Where all below ground traces have also been removed use DESTROYED MONUMENT."}

{"id": "71afeef3-29ab-4301-a313-38404a9c4f5c", "value": "A Monument whose presence is inferred from artefacts found in stratified below ground deposits, as distinct from surface collection or chance find."}

{"id": "7800d17e-c823-4c05-af8c-c8225a71fdc1", "value": "Monument either never or no longer visible above ground surface, but whose presence is indicated by proven below ground stratigraphy revealed by deliberate investigation, including geophysical survey, or other surface disturbance."}

{"id": "d6c98a4d-e8f8-432e-823c-0ee9a991a5dc", "value": "Monument visible as a mark in standing crops or parchmarks, but where no subsurface deposits have been proven eg by excavation or other ground disturbance, in which case SUB SURFACE DEPOSIT should be used."}

{"id": "8a0410c1-2b60-4d2b-98b7-8b4c1536ec2b", "value": "Maritime monument identified as a ferrous object lying on the sea bed detected using marine surveying equipment that detects localised anomalies in the Earth's magnetic field."}

{"id": "05aed6d6-dbc8-4aaf-ab3f-3dabe556cb0e", "value": "Monument whose existence is indicated by the discovery of isolated artefacts or an artefact scatter. Eg a scatter of roofing tiles indicating the presence of a building. Use narrow terms where circumstances of discovery are known."}

{"id": "6b63d5a7-7ee4-402f-b701-5894d73361b0", "value": "Monument existing as an upstanding earthwork, ditch or artificial watercourse, or as a low stone built feature not covered by the other categories."}
{"id": "4d095340-96d8-4d37-a95a-032d0486ff56", "value": "Monument visible as a below ground man-made structure. Use for tunnels, mineworking, cellars, shelters."}

{"id": "02d668d7-ec94-4537-b86a-b9b51c66f3dc", "value": "A monument where the evidence that defines the type of the monument derives from the nature of surface markings. Examples include graffitti on quarry walls."}
{"id": "3760cd78-cf51-46ab-a14f-71e8bab42e13", "value": "Man-made building, edifice or construction of assembled material parts."}

{"id": "a3127f3b-f4df-4e0f-8cf7-d69fa7e4d563", "value": "A landscape which has been specifically designed or modified. Often indicated by proven below ground stratigraphy, revealed by deliberate investigation including geophysical survey, or other surface monuments or structures."}
{"id": "5e6daff6-c63c-4a8d-a082-8fd43ce74871", "value": "Monument with a roof and walls or evidence of these."}
{"id": "c4bd8f44-ea0e-4a31-852b-0d7f59b1e7ae", "value": "Not to be used for indexing. Broad term used to assist retreival of all monuments where physical evidence is recorded."}

{"id": "a962a612-b9dc-43f6-a11a-80a2c46fdfa9", "value": "Monument whose existence is inferred from the traces of architectural features. Eg include shadow marks on building walls or beams, pillars, floors incorporated into a later structure, suggesting the existence of an earlier building."}
{"id": "960041dc-f5c5-4318-94ed-f087bc79f0df", "value": "Monument thought to be archaeological or historical but proved to be natural."}
{"id": "8266d63f-3582-4e53-bb5a-cf178129cddf", "value": "Feature visible following archaeological excavation"}

{"id": "28dff4b2-586e-47f2-acf9-d14dcc91077e", "value": "Monument visible, usually from the air, due to the fill of features being of a different colour than the surrounding subsoil. Soilmarks show up well in ploughed fields or areas where the topsoil has been stripped. Term derived from AN32 Glossary"}
{"id": "55c15429-1777-4fb1-90f1-891fb3b782cb", "value": "Natural feature or area deliberately enhanced to construct a monument, eg rock carving, cave, rock shelter."}
{"id": "87e0adf0-7709-4b0b-95b2-4366cc1af6fe", "value": "The fragmentary or substantial remains of a vehicle or aircraft. Where recovered from excavation double index with SUB SURFACE DEPOSIT."}

{"id": "7316d5b7-63f6-41bd-9d3a-e01e4677695c", "value": "A monument composed of plants or trees which are still extant. Especially relevant for park and garden features. For example tree avenue, orchard, rose garden and lawn."}
{"id": "ebb32488-58c1-43c8-99d9-f1aeef39382e", "value": "Monument visible on the sea, lake or river bed, either totally submerged at all times, or exposed at low tide, low water conditions etc."}

{"id": "525aebb9-a4f0-4f60-89f7-3bc8868eab71", "value": "Monument visible as substantial above ground remains, retaining evidence of architecture and materials, with walls partially or completely intact but with roof and interior walls substantially or completely destroyed."}
{"id": "0eca3b92-48b6-4f61-9eae-c4f0f17e3328", "value": "A maritime monument where the hull structure and fabric of a vessel remain wholly or mainly intact."}
{"id": "8178684e-92bf-43e1-b0cb-2c6cfe52d001", "value": "A maritime monument where the remains of a vessel are scattered over a wide area."}
{"id": "d72f1a40-403b-4fc1-b7bf-1b4562fde46e", "value": "A maritime monument where the vessel remains are buried in the sea bed."}
{"id": "ced223ff-27b0-46e8-b6be-27e62454e485", "value": "A maritime monument where the hull of a vessel is mostly in one piece, with large pieces of the superstructure intact."}
{"id": "e4ab1e4c-906e-470d-938c-ac5a3b9e979a", "value": "A maritime monument where the remains of a vessel are known to exist but where no detailed information is available."}
{"id": "511d3a58-893e-4fce-9ea9-1b8482cee774", "value": "A maritime monument where the fabric of a vessel has collapsed, leaving the hull structure flat on the sea bed but not widely dispersed."}
{"id": "79eedee3-7435-4a46-8669-cf068b654de7", "value": "Current recorded information does not give the evidence for a monument, or the information is regarded as unreliable."}

{"id": "5ed5b08a-740c-4753-b14f-6ff128bf6b3a", "value": "Man-made, roofless edifice or construction visible as substantial above-ground remains retaining evidence of architecture and materials, but which has been substantially destroyed."}
{"id": "453f97ed-2f8d-42bb-9b0c-37d7da5e6d34", "value": "Do not use"}

{"id": "ecc1b444-8686-4242-b7a2-19a4959bf912", "value": "All physical evidence for a monument has certainly been completely destroyed (allowing no future reinvestigation) by activity implying substantial ground disturbance. Eg quarrying, road cutting, or natural disaster, erosion, acts of God etc."}
{"id": "01423bf9-47ce-4944-8df8-ce68ded59025", "value": "Not to be used for indexing. Broad term to assist retreival of all monuments where non-physical evidence is recorded."}
{"id": "f3c466b3-1182-4d16-9dda-c4d47842d771", "value": "An object in the sea bed detected by marine survey equipment that shows the contours of the sea bed beneath a vessel."}

{"id": "f8a3e51e-3e9c-4bbe-964e-67956bbccdb6", "value": "A marine survey in which a multi-element transducer provides many (30-150) individual soundings of the water depth and echo strength for each ping."}
{"id": "51050a39-065c-4767-8e12-a3dfbf6f2eca", "value": "A monument visible as a trace on marine survey equipment"}
{"id": "e0a2f066-77ba-4d2a-a28f-2cdf9b851835", "value": "An object lying on the sea bed detected by marine survey equipment that emits and receives high frequency sound waves."}

{"id": "f3522472-8ec1-4585-ad6e-8f8b3faa1009", "value": "A monument consisting of a built structure, but which has been demolished so that only a ground plan and foundations, or similar, are thought to remain. Where all below ground traces have also been removed use DESTROYED MONUMENT."}

{"id": "7d9ca270-acbe-43df-a3f1-3049b9736565", "value": "Monument with roof or walls intact or substantially intact, significant survival of original features, even if building no longer in use for original function."}

{"id": "508bbba4-8b4b-4ff1-8062-c72f6fbe4a7a", "value": "A man-made construction or object (such as a gravestone) which has been moved from its original site either through active human intervention or natural processes such as erosion. For buildings which have been moved use MOVED BUILDING."}

{"id": "5bea2df1-2c46-4835-9c84-a84c360d6852", "value": "A building which has been moved from its original site either through active human intervention or natural processes such as erosion. For structures or objects such as gravestones use MOVED STRUCTURE."}
{"id": "48bebdd4-3612-47ad-9fdc-2c427f780d5d", "value": "An object in the sea bed recorded on the Hydrographic Office plot of objects snagged by nets during trawling."}

{"id": "a53260cd-8499-4405-b8e2-444823b7ee78", "value": "Monument type/interpretation is inferred, based on informed speculation eg by comparison with similar monuments, proximity to other monuments, topography, site character etc."}
{"id": "351c1114-b9e4-4a84-b13b-d0fe950267c9", "value": "A monument whose presence is inferred from verbally delivered information drawn from the speaker's personal knowledge."}
{"id": "0de4dd6b-1285-4cf1-98ef-e227a72c03f8", "value": "Monument whose presence is inferred by discovery of unstratified artefacts, for instance in plough soil."}

{"id": "227267fb-962e-49a9-b6f8-ecb694c6ea20", "value": "Monument known only from primary documentary sources eg books, maps, legal records, where no physical evidence exists. Use also where a monument has been planned but never constructed."}

{"id": "f16417a8-db54-461a-958b-a09114214223", "value": "Man-made roofless edifice or construction which is intact or substantially intant, with significant survival of original features, even if no longer serving original intended funtion."}
{"id": "a37a2f51-e1ed-4ee9-8d8e-bbf96e9e7639", "value": "Use where the presence or nature of a monument is inferred from placenames or placename elements."}
{"id": "34cc4f50-037e-423b-9ccb-5689aacbac95", "value": "A distribution of artefacts indicating the presence of former presence of a monument."}

{"id": "b402f4b8-cb74-49e2-9484-549e8f85c077", "value": "An object projecting out of the sea bed detected by marine survey equipment that emits and receives high frequency sound waves projected sideways from a boat or towed array."}
